Product Catalog Management

New and Changed Objects in Product Catalog Management

Users upgrading from Spring ‘24 must set field level security to access the new fields on the Product2 object.

Exclude attribute picklist values from product classification attributes and product attributes
Use the AttrPicklistExcludedValue object.
Get translated values for the product specification type’s label and description
Use the ProductSpecificationTypeLocalization object.
Define the quantity of a fulfillment order line item
Use the FulfillmentQtyCalcMethods field on the Product2 object.
Define the number of fulfillment order line items that must be generated
Use the DecompositionScope field on the Product2 object.
Adjust attribute value in increments or decrements at run time
Use the StepValue field on the ProductAttributeDefinition and ProductClassificationAttr objects.
Display attributes as sliders at run time
Use the Slider supported value in the Display Type field on the ProductAttributeDefinition and ProductClassificationAttr object.
Represent monetary and percentage-based attributes
Use the Currency and Percent supported values in the DataType field on the AttributeDefinition object.
